              <table width="98%" height="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" summary="layout table">
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" class="maintitle"><strong>MBS (Master of Business 
                    Studies), Postgraduate Diploma in Business Studies, Postgraduate 
                    Certificate in Business Studies</strong></td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <p>This course 
                      is designed for non-business graduates to expand business 
                      knowledge and skills and develop strategic thinking to enhance 
                      management performance. It is also appropriate for experienced 
                      managers to broaden theoretical understanding and enhance 
                      career prospects. The course covers key business functions 
                      including Human Resources, Marketing, Accountancy, Strategic 
                      and Operations Management.<br>
                      <strong><br>
                      </strong> <strong>Flexible study</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                      <li> Flexible entry routes; open to those with non-business 
                        degrees and those with substantial business expertise 
                        but no undergraduate qualification. Also suitable for 
                        career changers, teachers and those returning to work 
                        after a career break.</li>
                      <li> Exit points at Masters, Diploma or Certificate level 
                        to suit your requirements.</li>
                      <li> Covers key business functions including Human Resources; 
                        Marketing; Accountancy; Strategic and Operations Management.</li>
                      <li> Validated by the University of Leeds.</li>
                      <li> Full or part-time study, including evening sessions.</li>
                      <li> Return to study skills induction programme at the start 
                        of the course.</li>
                      <li> Use of an extensive range of management resources including 
                        business simulation packages, IT applications, CD-Rom 
                        databases and worldwide web intelligence services.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong> </strong> <strong>Course Structure </strong><br>
                      The programme is designed to be flexible and can be studied 
                      to Certificate, Diploma or Masters level depending on your 
                      circumstances and requirements. Full-time and part-time 
                      study and block release are available.</p>
                    <table width="93%" border="1">
                      <tr class="bodytext"> 
                        <td width="26%"><div align="center"></div></td>
                        <td width="35%"><div align="center"><strong>Full-time</strong></div></td>
                        <td width="39%"><div align="center"><strong>Part-time</strong></div></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="bodytext"> 
                        <td>Masters</td>
                        <td><div align="center">15 months</div></td>
                        <td><div align="center">2 years, 3 months</div></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="bodytext"> 
                        <td>Diploma</td>
                        <td><div align="center">9 months</div></td>
                        <td><div align="center">18 months</div></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr class="bodytext"> 
                        <td>Certificate</td>
                        <td><div align="center">6 months</div></td>
                        <td><div align="center">6 months</div></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <br>
                    The programme comprises three elements: core modules, option 
                    modules and a dissertation.<br> <br> <em>Core Modules </em><br> 
                    &#8226; Human Resource Management <br> &#8226; Marketing <br> 
                    &#8226; Accountancy <br> &#8226; Operations Management <br> 
                    &#8226; Strategic Management and Business Simulation <br> 
                    &#8226; Research Methods <br> &#8226; Dissertation 
                    <p><em>Option Modules </em><br>
                      A choice of two from: <br>
                      &#8226; E-commerce <br>
                      &#8226; Contemporary Organisational Issues <br>
                      &#8226; Economics of Markets and Industries <br>
                      &#8226; Financial Management 
                      <br>
                      &#8226; Law for Business Managers 
                      <br>
                      <br>
                      Specialist professional qualifications at Diploma level 
                      (or equivalent), may allow you exemption from appropriate 
                      core modules if relevant knowledge areas have been adequately 
                      covered. </p>
                    <p><strong>Assessment </strong><br>
                      Modules are assessed by a variety of methods including essays, 
                      seminar papers, reports, unseen examination papers and a 
                      dissertation based on an actual organisational situation, 
                      applying knowledge, understanding and skills successfully 
                      in a practical setting. For full-time students, this will 
                      normally include a placement within an external organisation 
                      to provide a suitable context for the dissertation. For 
                      part-time students, this will normally be conducted in your 
                      place of work if appropriate.<br>
                      <br>
                      <strong>Facilities and Resources </strong><br>
                      Extensive use of a range of IT applications focusing on 
                      professional systems and software, business databases, worldwide 
                      web business intelligence services and fully networked CD-Rom 
                      databases. A comprehensive range of management resources 
                      are available in Trinity &amp; All Saints and University 
                      of Leeds libraries.<br>
                      <strong><br>
                      </strong> <strong>Entry Requirements</strong><br>
                      &#8226; An honours degree (minimum 2.2) in any discipline 
                      <br>
                      &#8226; Or a professional award at Diploma level (or equivalent) 
                      together with three years employment/professional experience<br>
                      &#8226; Or A-level matriculation (or equivalent) together 
                      with six years employment/ professional experience<br>
                      &#8226; Or eight years post-18 employment/ professional 
                      (full time or substantially full-time permanent) experience. 
                      You may need to complete an Access course if you have no 
                      post-16 study experience or qualifications<br>
                      <br>
                      <br>
                      <strong>Contact Details</strong><br>
                      <br>
                      Course Director: Professor Keith Johnson<br>
                      For an informal discussion: 0113 283 7143<br>
                      Email: <a href="mailto:k.johnson@leedstrinity.ac.uk">k.johnson@leedstrinity.ac.uk</a> </p>
                    <p>For more information: <br>
                      Website: <a href="http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/business/mbs.htm">http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/business/mbs.htm<br>
                      </a>Tel: 0113 283 7268<br>
                      Fax: 0113 283 7321<br>
                      Email: <a href="mailto:admissions@leedstrinity.ac.uk">admissions@leedstrinity.ac.uk</a><br>
                    </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p>
